The paper deals with coding theory and the use of feedback to improve coding performance. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses controlled diffusions, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of feedback and optimization techniques also falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of simulations, which falls under the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of feedback in multimedia applications, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
